Time For a Pause In Leadership? @realmoney Recent declines in Senator Warren's poll standings have suggested that the progressive wing of the Democratic party is not quite as popular as previously thought. Lower polling standings have already led

to the Senator embracing a less ambitious health care narrative. Along with (and probably directly related) to her moderating polling status, has been an upward burst of share price strength in certain members (Facebook, Amazon and Google) of FANG and in the improving

performance of big money center bank shares. This is based on the notion of less onerous regulation than previously anticipated. My guess is that weakness in Senator Warren's polling is not entirely a statement about the progressive part of the Democratic party and might more

reflect the heightened popularity of Mayor Pete and the introduction of Mayor Bloomberg as a Presidential candidate. While I plan to keep medium sized positions in the stocks disclosed below - I expect the recent outperformance to begin to moderate from here. @jimcramer
Traders, with shorter term timeframes, may consider reducing now (or selling high priced calls against trading longs) in the hope of buying back cheaper in the future. Long BAC C WFC GS GOOGL AMZ
Depends on your trading/investing timeframe, Rev. Specifically, my timeframe is measured in months/years and not in days or weeks.
